<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,258,1867]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,350,258,283]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Taxonomic note:</emphasis>
The female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Salgueiro-Sepúlveda &amp; Álvarez-Padilla, 2018" authorityName="Salgueiro-Sepúlveda &amp; Álvarez-Padilla" authorityYear="2018" box="[524,613,259,283]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puya" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[524,613,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. puya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[620,684,258,283]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[620,684,258,283]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">n. sp.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
was previously described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Levi 1986" authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1986" box="[1015,1285,258,283]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chipinque">
<emphasis box="[1015,1158,258,283]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. chipinque</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[1167,1285,258,283]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" refId="ref14203" refString="Levi, H. (1986) The Neotropical orb-weaver genera Chrysometa and Homalometa (Araneae: Tetragnathidae). Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 151, 91 - 215." type="journal article">Levi 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; however the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1986" box="[267,412,294,319]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chipinque">
<emphasis box="[267,412,294,319]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. chipinque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to this new species taking into account the 
<collectionCode box="[1008,1056,295,319]" country="Portugal" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:14498" name="University of Coimbra Botany Department" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">COI</collectionCode>
analyses (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1261,294,319]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1532,1554]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,712,1500]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,698,1510]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 16. Phylogeny based on Maximum Likelihood analysis of the COI fragment gene of Chrysometa species. Values on branches indicate the bootstrap support. Branch length is proportional to nucleotide substitution rates." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444812/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
). Therefore the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1986" box="[264,407,330,355]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chipinque">
<emphasis box="[264,407,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. chipinque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by Levi is a misidentification.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
