<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,258,1867]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,510,535]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species epithet is from the Spanish word 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salgueiro-Sepúlveda &amp; Álvarez-Padilla" authorityYear="2018" box="[855,909,511,535]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puya">puya</taxonomicName>
(spur) and refers to the sharp projection of the cymbial ectomedian process in dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,258,1867]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,582,607]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salgueiro-Sepúlveda &amp; Álvarez-Padilla" authorityYear="2018" box="[475,567,583,606]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puya">
<emphasis box="[475,567,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. puya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1986" box="[899,1040,582,607]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palenque">
<emphasis box="[899,1040,582,607]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. palenque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and all sympatric species by the following features: epigynum transverse bar with curved arms and oval septum with convex sides protruding over the transverse bar (
<figureCitation box="[365,479,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figs. 11D</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Levi" authorityYear="1986" box="[500,746,654,679]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palenque">
<emphasis box="[500,746,654,679]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Chrysometa palenque</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
females have a shorter transverse bar with wide and rounded ends and straight sides of the septum. Males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Salgueiro-Sepúlveda &amp; Álvarez-Padilla" authorityYear="2018" box="[683,770,691,715]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puya">
<emphasis box="[683,770,691,715]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. puya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[1074,1236,690,715]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboguttata">
<emphasis box="[1074,1236,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">C. alboguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and all sympatric species by the following features: paracymbium large and thick with three upper prong lobes and two lower prong apophyses and a large and triangular cymbial ectomedian process (
<figureCitation box="[904,1014,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figs. 11G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1026,1144,763,787]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1526,1548]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,567,1492]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,555,1504]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Chrysometa puya n. sp., male. A, pedipalp ventral view. B, retrolateral view. C, dorsal view. Chrysometa sagicuta n. sp. Female. D, epigynum ventral view. E, posterior view. Scale bars, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444806/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">13A, B, C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[1164,1436,762,787]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Chrysometa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alboguttata">
<emphasis box="[1164,1436,762,787]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Chrysometa alboguttata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males have a bifurcated paracymbium with lower prong without apophyses and the cymbial ectomedian process flat and smaller.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,258,1867]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,870,895]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Description.</emphasis>
Female. Total length 3.7. Cephalothorax: length 2, width 1.4. Carapace pale-yellow, dark pattern over the cephalic region narrowing towards the fovea (
<figureCitation box="[778,883,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Ocular area pale-yellow. Eyes subequal in size (
<figureCitation box="[159,260,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 11E</figureCitation>
). AME diameter 0.11, PME 0.14, ALE and PLE 0.14. Chelicerae yellow, darker on sides and tips, few scattered setae (
<figureCitation box="[334,437,978,1003]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 11E</figureCitation>
). Endites longer than wide, brown, internal margins brighter. Labium wider than long, dark brown. Sternum yellow, darker sides, wider between the first and second legs (
<figureCitation box="[1107,1209,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Abdomen: brown, brighter on the center, dorsally covered with small guanine silvery patches, with transversal black patterns on the posterior part (
<figureCitation box="[316,449,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 11A, B</figureCitation>
); ventrally gray, with guanine patches on sides of the epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1277,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 11C</figureCitation>
). Leg lengths: I 8.1, II 6.7, 
<date box="[295,346,1123,1147]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">III 4</date>
and IV 5.5. Legs pale-yellow, darker on joints, with ventral and dorsal brown spots. Tarsi darkbrown. Epigynum: epigynal plate trapezoidal, wider than long; transverse bar more narrow below the septum, with curves arms. Septum oval with convex sides protruding over the transverse bar. margins well sclerotized. Copulatory openings small, on sides of the posterior part of the septum, not sclerotized (
<figureCitation box="[1139,1253,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figs. 11D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,258,1867]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
Male. As in female except as noted. Total length 3.4. Cephalothorax: length 1.8, width 1.5. Carapace brighter, brown rectangular pattern over the cephalic region, with darker margins. Ocular area darker. Chelicerae larger and narrower, with large teeth. Cuticle rugose, setae bases enlarged and more abundant at base (
<figureCitation box="[1214,1319,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
). Sternum pale-yellow. Abdomen: dorsally bright yellow, covered with guanine silvery patches uniformly distributed and without pattern defined; ventrally dark-gray, without guanine patches. Leg lengths: 
<date box="[1095,1141,1411,1435]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" value="2011-01">I 11</date>
, II 8.3, III 4.6 and IV 5.9. First pair darker. Tarsi brown. Pedipalp: 
<collectionCode box="[649,719,1447,1471]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">CEBP</collectionCode>
large and thin, pointing retrolaterally and spoon-shaped in retrolateral view. 
<collectionCode box="[355,431,1483,1507]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">CEMP</collectionCode>
large and triangular, rugose in ectal view. Paracymbium large and thick, with a large rounded three-lobed UpP and a small LwP with two apophysis in retrolateral view. Embolus thin and short, 
<collectionCode box="[1380,1436,1519,1543]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12977" name="Edinburgh Academy Field Centre" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">EBA</collectionCode>
short and curved in apical region; large, flattened and curved conductor (
<figureCitation box="[1026,1142,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figs. 11G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1159,1286,1555,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1526,1548]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,567,1492]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,555,1504]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Chrysometa puya n. sp., male. A, pedipalp ventral view. B, retrolateral view. C, dorsal view. Chrysometa sagicuta n. sp. Female. D, epigynum ventral view. E, posterior view. Scale bars, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444806/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">13A, B, C</figureCitation>
). Conductor, embolus and 
<collectionCode box="[300,356,1591,1615]" country="United Kingdom" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:12977" name="Edinburgh Academy Field Centre" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">EBA</collectionCode>
in ventral view as in 
<figureCitation box="[597,735,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1670,1692]" captionTargetBox="[162,1428,203,1639]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[151,1436,195,1649]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Chrysometa puya n. sp., female. A, habitus dorsal view. B, lateral view. C, ventral view. D, epigynum ventral view. E, prosoma anterior view. Male. F, prosoma anterior view. G, pedipalp ventral view. Scale bars, A, B, C, 1.0 mm; D, G, 0.2 mm; E, F, 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444802/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Figures 11G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[746,798,1591,1615]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1526,1548]" captionTargetBox="[171,1420,567,1492]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,555,1504]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Chrysometa puya n. sp., male. A, pedipalp ventral view. B, retrolateral view. C, dorsal view. Chrysometa sagicuta n. sp. Female. D, epigynum ventral view. E, posterior view. Scale bars, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1444806/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">13A</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,258,1867]" box="[199,956,1626,1651]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,316,1626,1651]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Variation.</emphasis>
Male total length 3.4–3.6, cephalothorax length 1.8–1.9.
</paragraph>
